Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "metra" in different forms and positions with translations in English:

1. *Metra* je mera za dužinu. (*Meter* is a unit of length.) 
2. Planina Everest je visoka 8,848 *metara*. (Mount Everest is 8,848 *meters* high.)
3. Treba mi *metar* papira da nacrtam planove. (I need a *meter* of paper to draw plans.)
4. Nivo buke u fabrici prelazi dozvoljenu granicu od 85 *decibela* na 2 *metra* udaljenosti. (The noise level in the factory exceeds the allowed limit of 85 *decibels* at a distance of 2 *meters*.)
5. Vozač kamiona treba da poštuje ograničenje brzine od 80 *kilometara* na *sat* na auto-putu. (The truck driver must obey the speed limit of 80 *kilometers* per *hour* on the highway.)
6. Moramo da postavimo ogradu od 50 *metara* oko zgrade. (We need to put up a fence of 50 *meters* around the building.)
7. Udaljenost između dva grada je oko 100 *kilometara*. (The distance between two cities is about 100 *kilometers*.)
8. Radnik je izmerio tačnu dužinu kabla - 12 *metara* i 15 *centimetara*. (The worker measured the exact length of the cable - 12 *meters* and 15 *centimeters*.)